# OurSay — repo-root environment template
#
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in. Each workspace loads the repo-root `.env`
# FIRST, then its own `.env` (local overrides). This root file is for variables shared
# across workspaces; workspace-specific config (immudb, Postgres, anchoring, etc.) lives
# in that workspace's own example so nothing pluggable/incomplete is pinned at the root:
#   - immudb-test/.env.example   (immudb + Postgres + spike anchoring vars)
#   - turnkey-test/.env.example  (Turnkey)
#
# NEVER commit real secrets. `.env` and `*.key.json` are gitignored.

# --- Turnkey (per-user wallets / per-thread keys) ---
# Shared because both turnkey-test and (later) the public-record identity layer use it.
TURNKEY_ORG_ID=
TURNKEY_API_PUB=
TURNKEY_API_PRIV=
# Optional: path (relative to repo root) to a Turnkey API key JSON with publicKey +
# privateKey fields. A `turnkey-api-credentials-*.key.json` at the repo root is
# auto-detected and overrides the values above.
# TURNKEY_API_KEY_FILE=./turnkey-api-credentials-XXXX.key.json
